==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Agio
<hw>Ag"i*o</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Agios</plw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[It. <ets>aggio</ets>
exchange, discount, premium, the same word as <ets>agio</ets> ease. See
Ease.]</ety> <fld>(Com.)</fld> <def>The premium or percentage on a
better sort of money when it is given in exchange for an inferior sort.
The premium or discount on foreign bills of exchange is sometimes called
<xex>agio</xex>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Agiotage</ent>⟦br⟧
